User & Access Management
Remove Unauthorized Local Users

Open Computer Management: Press Windows Key, type "Computer Management", press Enter
Navigate: System Tools → Local Users and Groups → Users
Right-click unauthorized user → Delete
Or via PowerShell: Remove-LocalUser -Name "<username>"

Remove Unauthorized Users from Administrator Group

In Computer Management → Local Users and Groups → Groups
Double-click "Administrators"
Compare with README authorized list
Select unauthorized user → Remove
Or via PowerShell: Remove-LocalGroupMember -Group "Administrators" -Member "<username>"

Disable Guest Account

In Computer Management → Local Users and Groups → Users
Right-click "Guest" → Properties
Check "Account is disabled" → OK
Or via PowerShell: Disable-LocalUser -Name "Guest"

Configure Password Policy

Press Windows Key + R, type secpol.msc, press Enter
Navigate: Account Policies → Password Policy
Double-click each setting and configure:

Password must meet complexity requirements: Enabled
Minimum password length: 8 characters (or as specified)
Maximum password age: 90 days
Minimum password age: 1 day
Enforce password history: 5 passwords remembered
Store passwords using reversible encryption: Disabled


Click OK for each

Configure Account Lockout Policy

Still in secpol.msc → Account Policies → Account Lockout Policy
Configure:

Account lockout threshold: 5 invalid attempts
Account lockout duration: 30 minutes
Reset account lockout counter after: 30 minutes


Click OK

Audit Group Memberships

Computer Management → Local Users and Groups → Groups
Check these groups: Administrators, Remote Desktop Users, Backup Operators, Power Users
Remove unauthorized members from sensitive groups

Authentication & Passwords
Change Administrator and User Passwords

Press Ctrl+Alt+Delete → Change Password
Or via Computer Management → Users → Right-click user → Set Password
Or PowerShell (run as admin):

powershell   $Password = Read-Host -AsSecureString "Enter new password"
   Set-LocalUser -Name "<username>" -Password $Password

Change for ALL authorized users

Enable Audit Policies

Open Local Security Policy (secpol.msc)
Navigate: Local Policies → Audit Policy
Enable these (Success and Failure):

Audit account logon events
Audit account management
Audit logon events
Audit policy change
Audit system events


Double-click each → Check both boxes → OK

Services & Features
Disable Unnecessary Services

Press Windows Key + R, type services.msc, press Enter
Review each service, identify unauthorized ones
Common services to check/disable if not needed:

Remote Registry
Telnet
FTP Publishing Service
Simple TCP/IP Services
World Wide Web Publishing Service (if not needed)


Double-click service → Startup type: Disabled → Stop → OK

Remove Prohibited Programs

Open Control Panel → Programs → Programs and Features
Or Settings → Apps → Installed apps
Look for: games, remote access tools (VNC, TeamViewer if unauthorized), P2P software
Right-click → Uninstall
Or PowerShell: Get-AppxPackage *<name>* | Remove-AppxPackage

Uninstall Unnecessary Windows Features

Open Server Manager
Click Manage → Remove Roles and Features
Click Next until Features page
Uncheck unnecessary features:

Telnet Client
TFTP Client
Simple TCP/IP Services
Any other unauthorized features


Click Next → Remove

Check Startup Programs

Press Ctrl+Shift+Esc (Task Manager)
Click "Startup" tab
Disable unauthorized startup items: Right-click → Disable
Also check: Press Windows + R → type shell:startup → Delete unauthorized items
Check Task Scheduler: taskschd.msc

Review Task Scheduler Library
Disable/delete suspicious tasks



Updates & Security
Run Windows Update

Open Settings: Windows Key + I
Windows Update → Check for updates
Install all available updates
Restart if required
Or via PowerShell:

powershell   Install-Module PSWindowsUpdate
   Get-WindowsUpdate
   Install-WindowsUpdate -AcceptAll -AutoReboot
Enable Windows Defender/Antivirus

Settings → Privacy & Security → Windows Security
Click "Virus & threat protection"
Ensure Real-time protection is ON
Click "Scan options" → Run Full scan
Manage settings → Ensure all protections are ON

Enable Windows Firewall

Press Windows Key, type "Windows Defender Firewall", press Enter
Click "Turn Windows Defender Firewall on or off"
Turn ON for all three profiles:

Domain networks
Private networks
Public networks


Click OK

Configure Automatic Updates

Settings → Windows Update
Click "Advanced options"
Ensure "Receive updates for other Microsoft products" is ON
Set Active hours to appropriate time
Or via Group Policy: gpedit.msc → Computer Configuration → Administrative Templates → Windows Components → Windows Update

Configure Automatic Updates: Enabled, Auto download and schedule install



File System & Permissions
Search for Prohibited Media Files

Open File Explorer → This PC
In search box (top right), search for:

*.mp3 - audio files
*.mp4 - video files
*.avi - video files
*.mov - video files
*.jpg - images (if prohibited)


Or PowerShell:

powershell   Get-ChildItem C:\ -Recurse -Include *.mp3,*.mp4,*.avi,*.mov -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

Delete if prohibited: Right-click → Delete

Check Scheduled Tasks

Press Windows Key, type "Task Scheduler", press Enter
Click "Task Scheduler Library"
Review all tasks for suspicious entries
Check task actions (look for scripts, unauthorized programs)
Delete suspicious tasks: Right-click → Delete

Review Share Permissions

Open Computer Management
System Tools → Shared Folders → Shares
Review each share
Remove unnecessary shares: Right-click → Stop Sharing
For necessary shares: Right-click → Properties → Share Permissions → Set appropriately (remove Everyone if present)

Audit File/Folder Permissions

Navigate to C:\Users in File Explorer
Right-click → Properties → Security tab
Ensure only appropriate users have access
Remove unauthorized users: Edit → Select user → Remove
Check critical folders: C:\Windows\System32, Program Files

Network Security
Review Firewall Rules

Press Windows Key, type "Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security", press Enter
Click "Inbound Rules"
Review each rule
Disable unauthorized rules: Right-click → Disable Rule
Delete if clearly malicious: Right-click → Delete
Repeat for "Outbound Rules"

Secure Remote Desktop

If not required: Disable RDP

Right-click This PC → Properties → Remote settings
Select "Don't allow remote connections" → OK


If required: Secure it

Only allow specific users: Select users → Add → Add authorized users only
Network Level Authentication should be required (checkbox)


Change RDP port (optional):

regedit → HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System\CurrentControlSet\Control\Terminal Server\WinStations\RDP-Tcp
Find "PortNumber" → Change from 3389 to another port



Check Listening Ports

Open PowerShell as Administrator
Run: netstat -ano | findstr LISTENING
Identify PIDs of unknown services
Find process: tasklist | findstr <PID>
Investigate and stop if unauthorized

Review Hosts File

Open Notepad as Administrator
File → Open → Navigate to: C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc
Change file type to "All Files"
Open "hosts" file
Remove suspicious entries (should mostly be localhost entries)
Save and close
